Architecture - MVP


Short architecture description

Application consists of three modules:

Model - module which is responsible for operations with data, such as - downloading data from internet, saving data to database and 
retrieving it. This module contains of classes for creating database and working with it using Room library, classes for tuning 
Retrofit and working with GitHub API.

View - module wherein take place data showing from database and occurs all kind of relative to UI actions - initializing views, 
showing loading and error messages to user, showing detailed information about picked from list repository.

Presenter - module that manages and controls work flow of application by using previous two modules, interacts with View using 
ViewInterface, interacts with Model for getting data to it and from it, directs data to View and controls it.

